How a researcher versions a metadata correction without copying the data — Tessera's content-addressed,
copy-on-write repository (ADR-0036). The `recon` study has the wrong tracer; the fix is one new version
whose image block is *shared* with the original (the copy is proportional to the change), then a clean
history-free artifact for handover. Runs in a sandbox seeded with `study.tsra`; ids are stable because
they are content hashes of the (fixed) inputs.

# === Initialize a content-addressed repository (objects + refs + log). ===

```
$ tessera init repo
initialized tessera repository at repo

```

# === Import the sealed study as the first version of its lineage (its stable `id`). ===

```
$ tessera import repo study.tsra
imported lineage blake3:12643649[..]
  version blake3:7c9f7bd9[..]

```

# === One version so far — the lineage tip. ===

```
$ tessera log repo blake3:12643649d5f63407dc00017950f2f1c94568e981339141da75df37cd35df2187
blake3:7c9f7bd9[..]  (tip)

```

# === Correct the metadata: commit a new version with `tracer=FDG`. The unchanged image block is reused
#     by digest — the new version writes one small object, not a second copy of the volume. ===

```
$ tessera commit repo blake3:12643649d5f63407dc00017950f2f1c94568e981339141da75df37cd35df2187 --set tracer=FDG
committed blake3:12643649[..]
  version    blake3:cb16e3ab2c645331e4f6b57a1b47a3a3654471184a20b3348b89d6adfb9fc1db
  supersedes blake3:7c9f7bd9[..]

```

# === History now has two versions, newest first. ===

```
$ tessera log repo blake3:12643649d5f63407dc00017950f2f1c94568e981339141da75df37cd35df2187
blake3:cb16e3ab2c645331e4f6b57a1b47a3a3654471184a20b3348b89d6adfb9fc1db  (tip)
blake3:7c9f7bd9[..]

```

# === What changed? Diff the tip against its parent — 0 blocks re-encoded, one metadata field added. ===

```
$ tessera diff repo blake3:c40501d7ef97e3aceda7a44273152c48ca23a905aa1c331a92a0eb6959fd2004
? 1
error: io: No such file or directory (os error 2)

```

# === Publish a history-free standalone `.tsra` for handover (drops the supersedes chain, keeps a
#     `snapshot_of` breadcrumb). ===

```
$ tessera publish repo blake3:c40501d7ef97e3aceda7a44273152c48ca23a905aa1c331a92a0eb6959fd2004 published.tsra
? 1
error: io: No such file or directory (os error 2)

```

# === The published artifact is a self-contained, verifiable product carrying the correction. ===

```
$ tessera verify published.tsra
? 1
error: io: No such file or directory (os error 2)

```
